p: As shown in Figure 4(a,b), EFEN exhibited inhibitory effects in a time-dependent manner. The half-maximal inhibition concentrations (IC 50) of EFEN were 6.79 μM, 1.95 μM, and 1.55 μM for 12 h, 24 h, and 48 h, respectively. Moreover, EFEN also exhibited inhibitory effects in a dose-dependent manner. The rates of suppression of tumor cells treated with EFEN for 24 h increased from 33% to 63% when EA concentrations increased from 2.5 μM to 20 μM.
